            <function>
                <term>The SOHC was founded to support the use of oral history within the academic
                    community as well as cognate areas such as archives and museums.</term>
            </function>
            <occupation><!--
                <descriptiveNote>The SOHC was founded to support the use of oral history within the
                    academic community as well as cognate areas such as archives and
                    museums.</descriptiveNote>-->
                <descriptiveNote>
                    <p>The SOHC was founded to support the use of oral history within the
                        academic community as well as cognate areas such as archives and
                        museums.</p>
                </descriptiveNote>
            </occupation>
            <biogHist>
                <p>The Scottish Oral History Centre (SOHC) was set up within the Department of
                    History at the University of Strathclyde in 1995. Since its foundation the SOHC
                    has been involved in a wide range of teaching, research and outreach activities
                    designed primarily to encourage the use of ‘best practice’ oral history
                    methodology in Scotland. Until 2005, the SOHC was directed by Professor Callum
                    Brown, since then by Professor Arthur McIvor.</p>
            </biogHist>
        </description>
